Viceroy Anguilla Creditors Seek Trustee to Run Bankruptcy Case

-- B y   M i c h a e l   B a t h o n
-- 
2011-04-14T16:36:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/viceroy-anguilla-creditors-seek-trustee-to-run-bankruptcy-case.html
Creditors of the owner of the
 Viceroy Anguilla Resort & Residences  on the British West Indies
island of Anguilla want to strip the company of control over its
bankruptcy case and appoint a trustee to take over.  The case is In re Barnes Bay Development Ltd., 11-10792,
 U.S. Bankruptcy Court , District of  Delaware  (Wilmington).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michael Bathon in Wilmington, Delaware, at 
 mbathon@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Pickering at   jpickering@bloomberg.net . 